paper_title: Temperature-dependent discovery of BCC refractory multi-principal element alloys: Integrating deep learning and CALPHAD calculations

claims.claim: At T = 1200 K, the trained model identified 6063 candidate compositions in the Ti–Fe–Al–V–Ni–Nb–Zr system (d = 0.03) as BCC with a predicted BCC volume fraction ≥ 0.9
instruction: The code normalizes the design space, feeds it into the trained model, and prints the number of BCC samples
The expected number of BCC samples is 6063
